COUTURE 2022

“The glamour of Calcutta. I can’t put a finger on it… it’s almost sexual and slightly dark. It comes from the very private chambers of the mind.”
 
Music: Cold by Anthony Lazaro
 
@farhanhussain, @kettlelove, @anthonylazaromusic, @sandhyashekar, @miteshrajani, @ravleen_.v, @rikeec, @shivangijulka_, @bhavs_gp, @oaktreepictures, @sabyasachijewelry, @sabyasachiaccessories #Sabyasachi #SabyasachiJewellery #SabyasachiAccessories #TheWorldOfSabyasachi

THE NEW COLLECTION

Featuring the Amherst Necklace from Sabyasachi High Jewellery’s Bengal Royale Collection. Paired with a printed organza sari.

@tarunvishwaofficial, @sandhyashekar, @miteshrajani, @sehazmalhi, @tajlakepalace
#Sabyasachi #TheWorldOfSabyasachi @sabyasachijewellery

THE BENGAL ROYALE COLLECTION
by Sabyasachi High Jewellery

“Growing up in Calcutta, I was fascinated by how the private was so much more exuberant than the public. Hand embroidered chemises and printed satin petticoats under humble cotton saris, decrepit homes with extravagant art and Osler chandeliers, and the most magnificent of terrazzo floors hidden beneath dusty carpets. Perhaps that is why the back of my jewellery is as lavish as the front.”

Featuring an emerald and diamond necklace. The back is intricately carved and studded with VVS diamonds.

#Sabyasachi #SabyasachiJewellery #TheWorldOfSabyasachi @sabyasachijewellery

THE CHOWRINGHEE SLING 
 by Sabyasachi Accessories

“Chowringhee is inextricable from the idea of Calcutta. The stuff of movies and novels, dreams and memory. A permanent sense of vintage. From the days of the Raj, where dissent and dissidence flowed alongside flappers and flaneurs. To reinventing Bengal between the excesses of the neo-Baroque and the audacity of Art Deco—Chowringhee has remained at the heart of it all. But it’s the subtle rebellions for me, just like the slight curve of the oval.” 

The Chowringhee Sling is crafted in fine Italian leather with the house insignia of the Bengal Tiger and a sling studded with carved tiger heads.

#Sabyasachi #SabyasachiAccessories ##TheWorldOfSabyasachi @sabyasachiaccessories

THE BENGAL ROYALE COLLECTION
by Sabyasachi High Jewellery

“Some of the most superlative jewellery ever made in India has been handcrafted by the master goldsmiths of Calcutta, colloquially known as the ‘Babus'. I want to make this legacy thrive again.”

Featuring a rubellite and diamond necklace. The back is intricately carved and studded with VVS diamonds.

#Sabyasachi #SabyasachiJewellery #TheWorldOfSabyasachi @sabyasachijewellery

THE NEW COLLECTION
 
Featuring the classic black silk sherwani with Sabyasachi monogram buttons and an embroidered silk organza shawl with marori embroidery. With a crafted diamond kilangi by Sabyasachi Heritage Jewellery and custom shoes by Sabyasachi Accessories.
 
Disclaimer: The kilangi has been made using faux feathers. At Sabyasachi we do not use real feathers in any of our products.
 
@kettlelove, @sandhyashekar, @miteshrajani, @saurabhchaudhary07, @sabyasachijewellery
#Sabyasachi #SabyasachiJewellery #TheWorldOfSabyasachi

THE LUCKNOW ROSE NECKLACE
From Sabyasachi High Jewellery’s Tropic of Calcutta Collection.

Featuring a deconstructed Maharani necklace crafted with uncut diamonds, sapphires, tourmalines, pearls, rubies, turquoise, aquamarines, garnets and rhodolites.

Article no SAB/22/004

#Sabyasachi #SabyasachiJewellery #TheWorldOfSabyasachi @sabyasachijewellery

SABYASACHI WHITE WEDDINGS
Clothing, Jewellery and Accessories
 
 
“Age-old marble palaces, handmade Swiss lace or my grandmother’s jamdani saris. I’ve always been fascinated by the deceptive simplicity of ivory on ivory. It is the epitome of understated but pure luxury.”
